ts thus far.....</span><hr size=1> It's pretty simple, really. After 50, you may choose to place a portion of the XP you earn into an &quot;Alternate Advancement&quot; bar. It takes the equivlent of 51 to 52 to fill this bar, but keep in mind that at higher levels this really isn't very much compared to what you can earn. Once you fill the bar, you get a point. If you die, XP is taken from your &quot;main&quot; XP bar only.<br>
<br>
In general, it's best to make 60 before fiddling with AA, but a lot of people are recommending doing the increased run speed thing even if you aren't 60 if you don't have Jboots and don't want to camp for them; since this is fairly simple to get and a great boon to getting 60 for a wizard, I can see why.<br>
<br>
Of course, lots of people don't care about efficency and want fun, so if you do go the AA route, it seems a lot of people think spell crits and the specialization enhancements are most useful.<br>
